@{
    @foreach (var brand in ViewBag.Tag)
    {
        ViewData["Title"] = @brand.TitleTag;
    }
}

@section MetaTags {
    @foreach (var brand in ViewBag.Tag)
    {
        <meta name="keywords" content="@brand.MetaKeywords" />
        <meta name="description" content="@brand.MetaDescription" />
    }
}
@foreach (var brand in ViewBag.Tag)
{
    <div class=" ">
        <h1 class="latest-bike-head">@brand.BrandName Bikes</h1>
        @*<h2 class="latest-bike-description p-b20">@brand.Discription</h2>*@
        <div class="brand-info-container">
            <div class="brand-info-content">

                <h3>Keeway Bikes in India 2025: Price, Mileage, Best Models & More</h3>

                <p class="brand-info-short">
                    In the world of two-wheelers, where design and individuality are becoming as important as practicality, Keeway has carved out a stylish niche. Originally a Hungarian brand with European roots, Keeway is now a globally recognized motorcycle and scooter manufacturer, offering a range of lifestyle-oriented bikes. In India, Keeway made its debut through Adishwar Auto Ride India (AARI), and it quickly turned heads with its bold cruisers, neo-retro commuters, and premium scooters.

                    Keeway is not about chasing mass numbers. Instead, it focuses on offering premium, eye-catching machines that bring a refreshing change to the Indian two-wheeler landscape. Whether you’re someone who values cruiser comfort, unique styling, or are simply looking to stand out on the road, Keeway bikes offer plenty of appeal in 2025.

                    In this article, we explore Keeway's bike price list, mileage figures, and top picks for long rides and fuel efficiency, and we also answer key questions that potential buyers may have.
                </p>

                <div class="brand-info-full" id="keewayMoreText">
                    <h3>Keeway Bikes Price List 2025 in India</h3>

                    <p>
                        Here is a look at the latest Keeway motorcycle and scooter models in India along with their estimated ex-showroom prices and mileage:
                    </p>

                    <div class="brand-table-wrapper">
                        <table class="brand-info-table">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Model</th>
                                    <th>Ex-Showroom Price (₹)</th>
                                    <th>Mileage (km/l)</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>

                            <tbody>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Keeway SR125</td>
                                    <td>₹1.20 lakh – ₹1.25 lakh</td>
                                    <td>45–50 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Keeway SR250</td>
                                    <td>₹1.49 lakh – ₹1.55 lakh</td>
                                    <td>35–40 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Keeway V302C</td>
                                    <td>₹3.89 lakh – ₹4.09 lakh</td>
                                    <td>28–32 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Keeway K-Light 250V</td>
                                    <td>₹3.19 lakh – ₹3.29 lakh</td>
                                    <td>30–35 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Keeway Vieste 300 (Scooter)</td>
                                    <td>₹3.29 lakh – ₹3.39 lakh</td>
                                    <td>30–35 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>Keeway Sixties 300i</td>
                                    <td>₹3.29 lakh – ₹3.39 lakh</td>
                                    <td>30–33 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        <i>Note: Prices and mileage may vary depending on variant, city, and riding style.</i>
                    </p>
                    <h3>Which Keeway Is Best for Long Rides?</h3>

                    <p>
                        Keeway may not have traditional touring bikes, but some of its cruisers and scooters are perfect for relaxed long-distance rides. These models are built with comfort in mind, and their unique styling makes them stand out on every highway stretch.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong class="brand-sub-heading">Top Keeway Bikes for Long-Distance Riding:</strong>
                    </p>

                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Keeway V302C</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>A classic low-slung cruiser with a powerful 298cc V-twin engine</li>
                                <li>Features include a wide handlebar, low seat height, and dual exhausts</li>
                                <li>Built for comfortable highway cruising with a strong visual presence</li>
                                <li>Ideal for riders who love laid-back weekend touring</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Keeway K-Light 250V</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Mid-size cruiser with a retro look and smooth engine characteristics</li>
                                <li>Suitable for daily rides and occasional highway sprints</li>
                                <li>Strong torque delivery in the low end — great for a relaxed pace</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Keeway Vieste 300 (Maxi-Scooter)</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Touring-style scooter with ample legroom, under-seat storage, and wide seats</li>
                                <li>Automatic CVT gearbox — perfect for city and highway commuting</li>
                                <li>Great for riders who want convenience with long-distance capability</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        All of these models offer comfort-focused ergonomics and stylish road presence, making Keeway a solid pick for cruiser lovers and highway roamers.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Which Keeway Has the Best Mileage?</h3>

                    <p>
                        While Keeway leans more toward premium cruiser and style-focused models, it also offers a couple of lightweight commuters that deliver respectable fuel efficiency.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong class="brand-sub-heading">Top Mileage Keeway Bikes in India:</strong>
                    </p>

                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Keeway SR125</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Mileage: 45–50 km/l</li>
                                <li>Retro-style commuter with a 125cc engine</li>
                                <li>Lightweight, fuel-efficient, and ideal for daily urban rides</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Keeway SR250</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Mileage: 35–40 km/l</li>
                                <li>Larger than the SR125 with slightly more punch</li>
                                <li>Still economical and suited for urban + occasional highway use</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        Both of these bikes offer decent mileage for those looking at Keeway as a stylish yet practical alternative in the commuter category.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Why Is Keeway Famous?</h3>

                    <p>
                        Keeway may be new to India, but its bold designs and niche offerings have already earned it attention. Unlike mass-market competitors, Keeway focuses on lifestyle and uniqueness, positioning itself as a brand for the rider who wants to be different.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong class="brand-sub-heading">Key Reasons for Keeway’s Popularity:</strong>
                    </p>

                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Stylish Cruiser Aesthetics</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>V-twin engines, dual exhausts, and low-slung frames create true-blue cruiser appeal</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Retro-Modern Design Language</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The SR125, SR250, and Sixties 300i mix old-school style with modern tech</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Maxi-Scooter Appeal</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Vieste 300 is one of the few premium scooters offering power + comfort</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>European Brand Identity</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Hungarian origin lends it a distinctive European brand vibe</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Premium Features</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>LED lights, digital consoles, dual-channel ABS, and belt-drive (on some models)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Niche Positioning</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Appeals to style-conscious buyers who want something other than typical sports or commuter bikes</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                    </ul>
                    <h3>Final Thoughts</h3>

                    <p>
                        Keeway has brought a refreshing twist to India’s two-wheeler market. It doesn’t compete in the commuter mainstream or aggressive sportbike space. Instead, it delivers style-first machines with premium appeal, targeting those who prioritize design, comfort, and presence.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Whether you’re a city commuter looking for retro flair or a rider planning weekend getaways on a V-twin cruiser, Keeway’s lineup in 2025 has something unique to offer. With expanding service support and growing brand awareness, Keeway could be the next big name for niche motorcycling in India.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Top 10 FAQs About Keeway Bikes in India (2025)</h3>

                    <div class="faq-container">

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>1. Is Keeway a Chinese or European brand?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Keeway is originally a Hungarian brand, now globally managed with Chinese manufacturing partnerships.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>2. Which Keeway bike is best for touring?</h4>
                            <p>
                                The V302C and K-Light 250V are ideal cruisers for long-distance rides.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>3. Is Keeway a good brand in India?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yes, Keeway offers premium and unique models that fill niche segments in India.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>4. Which Keeway bike has the best mileage?</h4>
                            <p>
                                The SR125 offers the best mileage at around 45–50 km/l.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>5. Are Keeway scooters good for daily use?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yes, the Vieste 300 is a powerful and stylish scooter great for daily and occasional long rides.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>6. What’s special about the Keeway V302C?</h4>
                            <p>
                                It’s one of the few sub-400cc V-twin cruisers in India, offering a real cruiser experience.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>7. Does Keeway offer ABS in its bikes?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yes, most Keeway bikes come equipped with dual-channel ABS for safety.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>8. Where can I buy a Keeway bike in India?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Keeway bikes are available through authorized dealerships across major cities.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>9. Is Keeway expensive to maintain?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Being a premium brand, costs may be slightly higher than commuter bikes, but support is expanding rapidly.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>10. What makes Keeway different from other bike brands?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Keeway focuses on unique styling, cruiser formats, and lifestyle products rather than mass-market models.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                    </div>
                </div>
                <button class="brand-read-btn"
                        onclick="toggleBrandInfo('keewayMoreText', this)">
                    Read More
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
        <script>function toggleBrandInfo(contentId, button) {

                const content = document.getElementById(contentId);

                if (content.style.display === "block") {

                    content.style.display = "none";
                    button.innerText = "Read More";

                } else {

                    content.style.display = "block";
                    button.innerText = "Read Less";
                }
            }</script>
    </div>
 }
@await Html.PartialAsync("_BrandComponent")
@await Html.PartialAsync("_AllComponent")
